## Summary

HARDEN pass on **F6_bill_integrity_structural** (AT target, L2→L2) — the drawn Rule-0 self-refill work. Two genuine findings, both closed:

1. **R15 kill-list honesty gap (closed).** The three load-bearing Tier-1 structural controls (`check_bill_foots`, `check_bill_line_items_non_negative`, `check_bill_period_sane`) were F6's L2 evidence but had firing tests *only* in the atom's own test files — they were never entered in the central mutation-test apparatus (`tests/controls/test_control_mutation.py` + `control_registry.json`), so the published kill-list count silently excluded them. Now registered and mutation-tested there; all three FIRE. Cumulative kill list: 29→32 tested / 28→31 fired / 1 theatre unchanged. Proof-door data (`site/data/control_kill_list.json`) and `CONTROL_KILL_LIST.md` brought current.

2. **Red-team finding + fix (FAIL-OPEN closed).** `check_bill_period_sane` — the "temporal sanity" control — checked `start <= end` **only**, so an ordered-but-multi-decade period (`2024-01-01 → 2099-12-31`) sailed through the very absurdity class it's named for. Fixed as a class invariant (R10): a span > `_MAX_BILL_PERIOD_DAYS` (731 days, ~24× the 30-day observed real-data max; back-billing windows use the separate `catchup_period_*` fields) now fails CLOSED. **Verified outcome-safe: 1587 real bills, 0 newly HELD.** One named residual left honest (R10): a wholly-future normal-span period stays uncaught because the predicate is deliberately clock-free (C-S2 replay-safe) — registered as follow-up, not smuggled in.

Gates: 1670 tests pass across the billing/compliance/controls/tools blast radius, epistemic verifier PASS. Pushed to origin/main, SHA confirmed.

